42static isccc_sexpr_t sexpr_t = { ISCCC_SEXPRTYPE_T, { NULL } };
43
44#define CAR(s) (s)->value.as_dottedpair.car
45#define CDR(s) (s)->value.as_dottedpair.cdr
46
47isccc_sexpr_t *
48isccc_sexpr_cons(isccc_sexpr_t *car, isccc_sexpr_t *cdr) {
49 isccc_sexpr_t *sexpr;
50
51 sexpr = malloc(sizeof(*sexpr));
52 if (sexpr == NULL)
53 return (NULL);
54 sexpr->type = ISCCC_SEXPRTYPE_DOTTEDPAIR;
55 CAR(sexpr) = car;
56 CDR(sexpr) = cdr;
57
58 return (sexpr);
59}
60
61isccc_sexpr_t *
62isccc_sexpr_tconst(void) {
63 return (&sexpr_t);
64}
65
66isccc_sexpr_t *
67isccc_sexpr_fromstring(const char *str) {
68 isccc_sexpr_t *sexpr;
69
70 sexpr = malloc(sizeof(*sexpr));
71 if (sexpr == NULL)
72 return (NULL);
73 sexpr->type = ISCCC_SEXPRTYPE_STRING;
74 sexpr->value.as_string = strdup(str);
75 if (sexpr->value.as_string == NULL) {
76 free(sexpr);
77 return (NULL);
78 }
79
80 return (sexpr);
81}
82
83isccc_sexpr_t *
84isccc_sexpr_frombinary(const isccc_region_t *region) {
85 isccc_sexpr_t *sexpr;
86 unsigned int region_size;
87
88 sexpr = malloc(sizeof(*sexpr));
89 if (sexpr == NULL)
90 return (NULL);
91 sexpr->type = ISCCC_SEXPRTYPE_BINARY;
92 region_size = REGION_SIZE(*region);
93 /*
94 * We add an extra byte when we malloc so we can NUL terminate
95 * the binary data. This allows the caller to use it as a C
96 * string. It's up to the caller to ensure this is safe. We don't
97 * add 1 to the length of the binary region, because the NUL is
98 * not part of the binary data.
99 */
100 sexpr->value.as_region.rstart = malloc(region_size + 1);
101 if (sexpr->value.as_region.rstart == NULL) {
102 free(sexpr);
103 return (NULL);
104 }
105 sexpr->value.as_region.rend = sexpr->value.as_region.rstart +
106 region_size;
107 memmove(sexpr->value.as_region.rstart, region->rstart, region_size);
108 /*
109 * NUL terminate.
110 */
111 sexpr->value.as_region.rstart[region_size] = '\0';
112
113 return (sexpr);
114}
115
116void
117isccc_sexpr_free(isccc_sexpr_t **sexprp) {
118 isccc_sexpr_t *sexpr;
119 isccc_sexpr_t *item;
120
121 sexpr = *sexprp;
122 if (sexpr == NULL)
123 return;
124 switch (sexpr->type) {
125 case ISCCC_SEXPRTYPE_STRING:
126 free(sexpr->value.as_string);
127 break;
128 case ISCCC_SEXPRTYPE_DOTTEDPAIR:
129 item = CAR(sexpr);
130 if (item != NULL)
131 isccc_sexpr_free(&item);
132 item = CDR(sexpr);
133 if (item != NULL)
134 isccc_sexpr_free(&item);
135 break;
136 case ISCCC_SEXPRTYPE_BINARY:
137 free(sexpr->value.as_region.rstart);
138 break;
139 }
140 free(sexpr);
141
142 *sexprp = NULL;
143}
144
145static bool
146printable(isccc_region_t *r) {
147 unsigned char *curr;
148
149 curr = r->rstart;
150 while (curr != r->rend) {
151 if (!isprint(*curr))
152 return (false);
153 curr++;
154 }
155
156 return (true);
157}
158
159void
160isccc_sexpr_print(isccc_sexpr_t *sexpr, FILE *stream) {
161 isccc_sexpr_t *cdr;
162 unsigned int size, i;
163 unsigned char *curr;
164
165 if (sexpr == NULL) {
166 fprintf(stream, "nil");
167 return;
168 }
169
170 switch (sexpr->type) {
171 case ISCCC_SEXPRTYPE_T:
172 fprintf(stream, "t");
173 break;
174 case ISCCC_SEXPRTYPE_STRING:
175 fprintf(stream, "\"%s\"", sexpr->value.as_string);
176 break;
177 case ISCCC_SEXPRTYPE_DOTTEDPAIR:
178 fprintf(stream, "(");
179 do {
180 isccc_sexpr_print(CAR(sexpr), stream);
181 cdr = CDR(sexpr);
182 if (cdr != NULL) {
183 fprintf(stream, " ");
184 if (cdr->type != ISCCC_SEXPRTYPE_DOTTEDPAIR) {
185 fprintf(stream, ". ");
186 isccc_sexpr_print(cdr, stream);
187 cdr = NULL;
188 }
189 }
190 sexpr = cdr;
191 } while (sexpr != NULL);
192 fprintf(stream, ")");
193 break;
194 case ISCCC_SEXPRTYPE_BINARY:
195 size = REGION_SIZE(sexpr->value.as_region);
196 curr = sexpr->value.as_region.rstart;
197 if (printable(&sexpr->value.as_region)) {
198 fprintf(stream, "'%.*s'", (int)size, curr);
199 } else {
200 fprintf(stream, "0x");
201 for (i = 0; i < size; i++)
202 fprintf(stream, "%02x", *curr++);
203 }
204 break;
205 default:
206 INSIST(0);
207 ISC_UNREACHABLE();
208 }
209}

211isccc_sexpr_t *
212isccc_sexpr_car(isccc_sexpr_t *list) {
213 REQUIRE(list->type == ISCCC_SEXPRTYPE_DOTTEDPAIR);
214
215 return (CAR(list));
216}

218isccc_sexpr_t *
219isccc_sexpr_cdr(isccc_sexpr_t *list) {
220 REQUIRE(list->type == ISCCC_SEXPRTYPE_DOTTEDPAIR);
221
222 return (CDR(list));
223}

225void
226isccc_sexpr_setcar(isccc_sexpr_t *pair, isccc_sexpr_t *car) {
227 REQUIRE(pair->type == ISCCC_SEXPRTYPE_DOTTEDPAIR);
228
229 CAR(pair) = car;
230}

232void
233isccc_sexpr_setcdr(isccc_sexpr_t *pair, isccc_sexpr_t *cdr) {
234 REQUIRE(pair->type == ISCCC_SEXPRTYPE_DOTTEDPAIR);
235
236 CDR(pair) = cdr;
237}

239isccc_sexpr_t *
240isccc_sexpr_addtolist(isccc_sexpr_t **l1p, isccc_sexpr_t *l2) {
241 isccc_sexpr_t *last, *elt, *l1;
242
243 REQUIRE(l1p != NULL);
244 l1 = *l1p;
245 REQUIRE(l1 == NULL || l1->type == ISCCC_SEXPRTYPE_DOTTEDPAIR);
246
247 elt = isccc_sexpr_cons(l2, NULL);
248 if (elt == NULL)
249 return (NULL);
250 if (l1 == NULL) {
251 *l1p = elt;
252 return (elt);
253 }
254 for (last = l1; CDR(last) != NULL; last = CDR(last))
255 /* Nothing */;
256 CDR(last) = elt;
257
258 return (elt);
259}

261bool
262isccc_sexpr_listp(isccc_sexpr_t *sexpr) {
263 if (sexpr == NULL || sexpr->type == ISCCC_SEXPRTYPE_DOTTEDPAIR)
264 return (true);
265 return (false);
266}

269isccc_sexpr_emptyp(isccc_sexpr_t *sexpr) {
270 if (sexpr == NULL)
271 return (true);
272 return (false);
273}

276isccc_sexpr_stringp(isccc_sexpr_t *sexpr) {
277 if (sexpr != NULL && sexpr->type == ISCCC_SEXPRTYPE_STRING)
278 return (true);
279 return (false);
280}

282bool
283isccc_sexpr_binaryp(isccc_sexpr_t *sexpr) {
284 if (sexpr != NULL && sexpr->type == ISCCC_SEXPRTYPE_BINARY)
285 return (true);
286 return (false);
287}

289char *
290isccc_sexpr_tostring(isccc_sexpr_t *sexpr) {
291 REQUIRE(sexpr != NULL &&
292 (sexpr->type == ISCCC_SEXPRTYPE_STRING ||
293 sexpr->type == ISCCC_SEXPRTYPE_BINARY));
294
295 if (sexpr->type == ISCCC_SEXPRTYPE_BINARY)
296 return ((char *)sexpr->value.as_region.rstart);
297 return (sexpr->value.as_string);
298}
299
300isccc_region_t *
301isccc_sexpr_tobinary(isccc_sexpr_t *sexpr) {
302 REQUIRE(sexpr != NULL && sexpr->type == ISCCC_SEXPRTYPE_BINARY);
303 return (&sexpr->value.as_region);
304}
